Subject: [PATCH 394/974] MIPS: cavium-octeon: fix early boot hang on EBH5600
 board

The boot hangs early on EBH5600 board when octeon_fdt_pip_iface() is
trying enumerate a non-existant interface. The actual hang happens in
cvmx_helper_interface_enumerate().

when interface == 4. We can avoid this situation by first checking that
the interface exists in the DTB.

Signed-off-by: Aaro Koskinen <aaro.koskinen@nsn.com>
[david.daney@cavium.com] Ported to current sources.
Signed-off-by: David Daney <david.daney@cavium.com>
[Original patch taken from Cavium SDK 3.1.2-568]
Signed-off-by: Quanyang Wang <quanyang.wang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/cavium-octeon/octeon-platform.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/octeon-platform.c b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/octeon-platform.c
index 32d2f2d..d20e878 100644
--- a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/octeon-platform.c
+++ b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/octeon-platform.c
@@ -237,13 +237,13 @@ static void __init octeon_fdt_pip_iface(int pip, int idx, u64 *pmac)
 	int p;
 	int count;
 
-	count = cvmx_helper_interface_enumerate(idx);
-
 	snprintf(name_buffer, sizeof(name_buffer), "interface@%d", idx);
 	iface = fdt_subnode_offset(initial_boot_params, pip, name_buffer);
 	if (iface < 0)
 		return;
 
+	count = cvmx_helper_interface_enumerate(idx);
+
 	for (p = 0; p < 16; p++)
 		octeon_fdt_pip_port(iface, idx, p, count - 1, pmac);
 }
